# Cloudflare Pages redirect rules. Vite copies this file verbatim from public/
# into the build output (dist/_redirects). Evaluated top-to-bottom; first match
# wins. Clean URLs (e.g. /species → species.html) are handled natively by Pages.
#
# NOTE: Pages `_redirects` only matches on PATH, not hostname — a cross-host rule
# here (www → apex) is silently ignored, so that redirect lives in
# functions/_middleware.js instead. Only path-based rules belong in this file.

